    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-olive-spaghetti-with-caper-crumb/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-olive-spaghetti-with-caper-crumb/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of\u00a0<strong>olive oil</strong>\u00a0over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once the pan is hot, add your <strong>roasted garlic paste </strong>and <strong>halved cherry tomatoes </strong>and cook for 3-4 min until the tomatoes have started to break down</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-olive-spaghetti-with-caper-crumb/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>pasta</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>pasta</strong> for 7-9 min (10\u201312 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>pasta</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong>, then return to the pot with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and set aside until later</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-olive-spaghetti-with-caper-crumb/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pasta is cooking, add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>,<strong> half</strong> your <strong>capers</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> to a tray</p><p>Give it all a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 3-4 min until lightly toasted and golden \u2013 this is your <strong>caper crumb</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and the <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-olive-spaghetti-with-caper-crumb/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the\u00a0tomatoes have started to break down, add your <strong>black</strong> <strong>olives</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>remaining capers </strong>and <strong>tomato stock </strong>to the pan and cook for 2-3 min further</p><p>Add a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato & olive sauce</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if the sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-olive-spaghetti-with-caper-crumb/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen<strong> </strong>paper and dress\u00a0with your\u00a0<strong>balsamic vinegar</strong>\u00a0and a drizzle of\u00a0<strong>olive oil </strong>in a bowl \u2013 this is your<strong> dressed salad</strong></p><p>Chop your\u00a0<strong>parsley</strong>\u00a0finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-olive-spaghetti-with-caper-crumb/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>tomato & olive sauce</strong> over the <strong>cooked pasta </strong>with the <strong>dressed salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped parsley</strong> and sprinkle over the <strong>caper crumb</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
